quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  65,1,"O Prophet, when you<sup>pl </sup>divorce{1}women, then divorce them at a time when their<i>(waiting) </i>period can properly start, and calculate the period carefully. And be mindful of Allah, your<sup>pl </sup>Lord. Do not evict them from their houses nor shall they depart, unless they have committed an evident obscenity{2}. Those are the limits of Allah, and whoever oversteps Allah’s limits, then he has surely been unjust to himself. You<sup>sg </sup>never know—Allah may afterwards bring about a new matter.",footnotes:1:[It is obvious from the masculine plural pronoun that the Qur’an is addressing men.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Ibn Kathir and Shu’ba read it as: “…committed an evidenced obscenity.”]
  65,2,"Once they have reached their term, either retain<sup>pl </sup>them in accordance with what is fair or separate from them in accordance with what is fair. And call to witness two just people from among you and give upright testimony for Allah. That is to admonish whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day, for whoever is mindful of Allah—He will make for him a way out<i>(of every difficulty) </i>"
  65,3,"and will provide for him from where he never expects, and whoever places his trust in Allah—He will suffice him. Allah shall indeed conclude His decreed matters; Allah has set a due measure for everything."
  65,4,"And those of your womenwho have despaired of<i>(further) </i>menstruation—if you have any doubts, their<i>(waiting) </i>period shall be three months, and also for those who have not menstruated{1}. And those who are pregnant—their term shall be until they have delivered. And whoever is mindful of Allah—He will ease his affairs.",footnotes:1:Puberty is a condition for marriage in Islam; some women do not menstruate because of abnormalities of the reproductive tract.
  65,5,"That is Allah’s command which He has sent down to you<sup>pl </sup>. And whoever is mindful of Allah—He will remit his evil deeds and amplify his reward."
